    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pure, artificial calcium carbonate; frequently a by-product of drug and chemical manufacturing. Used industrially as an inert pigment, as well as in gesso grounds and pastel crayons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carbonato de calcio puro, artificial, a menudo subproducto de la industria farmacéutica y química. Se utiliza industrialmente como pigmento inerte, como base de gesso y en lápices pastel.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Puur, kunstmatig calciumcarbonaat, vaak een afvalproduct bij de vervaardiging van medicijnen en chemische producten. Het wordt in de industrie gebruikt als een inert pigment of in gesso onderlagen en pastelkrijt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種質純的人造碳酸鈣，通常為藥品及化學物質製造過程的副產物。工業上當作惰性顏料使用，也做為石膏底材及粉彩蠟筆。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
